Key Match Events: Devon Conway's innings came from just 58 balls with seven fours and two sixes
Finn Allen scored 42 off just 16 balls
Mitchell Santner and Tim Southee both took three wickets each
New Zealand's first win against Australia in Australia since 2011
Mitchell Marsh was caught by Phillips going for another slog
Phillips pulled off one of the catches of the tournament so far to remove Stoinis for seven
Post-Match Reflections: A special performance from the boys, said man of the match Conway
Victory over Australia on any occasion is a big up for us, added Conway
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match at a sold-out Sydney Cricket Ground was a repeat of the 2021 final in Dubai
David Warner fell for three in the second over
Finch hit a giant six off Trent Boult but didn't last much longer
Phillips became Santner's third wicket, out for 11, leaving Australia teetering at 68-5 in the 11th over
Matthew Wade (two) and Glenn Maxwell (28) were their last hope with the tailenders offering little resistance
